                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Combs</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-10-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister of Ecuador at Lima has formally by note presented proposition for direct
                    negotiations. Minister for foreign affairs of Peru will probably decline to
                    consider it or any proposition, relying on mediators for solution.</p>
                <p>It is thought Ecuador will base on this refusal a renunciation of arbitration
                    treaty of 1887.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Combs.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
